Mental Health and Support App

This is a Vanilla JavaScript application built using Vite as the development environment. The app aims to promote mental health and provide resources for support. It integrates several interactive and animated features using modern libraries and tools.

Features

Interactive Vector Animations: Powered by Rive.

Advanced Animations: Smooth animations implemented using GSAP.

Lottie Files: Used for animated vector illustrations.

3D Model Integration: Utilizes Model Viewer for showcasing 3D models.

Chart Integration: Displays data visually using Chart.js.

Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following installed on your system:

Node.js (v14 or later recommended)

npm (comes with Node.js)

Getting Started

Follow these steps to set up and run the project:

1. Clone the Repository

# Clone this repository
$ git clone <repository-url>

# Navigate to the project directory
$ cd <project-directory>

2. Install Dependencies

# Install the required packages
$ npm install

3. Run the Development Server

# Start the development server
$ npm run dev

4. Access the App

After running the development server, open your browser and navigate to:

http://localhost:5173

Libraries and Tools Used

Vite:

Fast and lightweight development server.

Rive:

Interactive vector animations.

Documentation: Rive.app

GSAP:

GreenSock Animation Platform for robust animations.

Documentation: greensock.com

Lottie Files:

Animated vector illustrations using JSON-based animation files.

Documentation: LottieFiles.com

Model Viewer:

Integration of 3D models into the app.

Documentation: modelviewer.dev

Chart.js:

Visual representation of data using charts.

Documentation: chartjs.org

Project Goals

This application aims to provide an interactive and visually engaging platform for:

Educating users about mental health.

Offering resources and support mechanisms.

Encouraging a community-driven approach to mental well-being.

Development Notes

Scripts

npm install: Installs project dependencies.

npm run dev: Starts the development server.

npm run build: Builds the app for production.


